{"lemma":"رَزَّ","slug":"رَزَّ","root":"ر.ز.ز","root_slug":"ر-ز-ز","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ز-ز","pos":"V","pos_camel":"verb","paradigm":[{"role":"past_2ms","form":"رَزَزْتَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"past_2fs","form":"رَزَزْتِ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"past_2md","form":"رَزَزْتُما","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"past_2mp","form":"رَزَزْتُم","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"past_2fp","form":"رَزَزْتُنَّ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"past_3ms","form":"رَزَّ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"past_3fs","form":"رَزَّت","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"past_3md","form":"رَزّا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"past_3fd","form":"رَزَّتا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"d"},{"role":"past_3mp","form":"رَزُّوا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"past_3fp","form":"رَزَزْنَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"present_2ms","form":"تَرُزّ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_2ms","form":"تَرْزُز","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_2fs","form":"تَرُزِّي","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"present_2fs","form":"تَرُزِّينَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"present_2md","form":"تَرُزّا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_2md","form":"تَرُزّانِ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_2mp","form":"تَرُزُّوا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_2mp","form":"تَرُزُّونَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_2fp","form":"تَرْزُزْنَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"present_3ms","form":"يَرُزّ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_3ms","form":"يَرْزُز","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_3fs","form":"تَرُزّ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"present_3fs","form":"تَرْزُز","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"present_3md","form":"يَرُزّا","in_corpus":true,"count":1,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3md","form":"يَرُزّانِ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3fd","form":"تَرُزّا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3fd","form":"تَرُزّانِ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3mp","form":"يَرُزُّوا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_3mp","form":"يَرُزُّونَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_3fp","form":"يَرْزُزْنَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"present_1mp","form":"نَرُزّ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_1ms","form":"أَرُزّ","in_corpus":true,"count":1,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"past_1mp","form":"رَزَزْنا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"past_1ms","form":"رَزَزْتُ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"s"}],"frequency_in_corpus":2,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n15348","n15349"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%B2%D9%8E%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"rice","examples":[{"text":"والوجه الآخر إن يقطع له الأرض أمشارا أمشارا ويدخل فيها الماء ويقام فيها مقدار شبرة ثم ينثر الحب عليه نثرا وإذا شربت الأرض ذلك الماء غطي الرز برقيق التراب ينثر علبه بالأيادي حتى إذا مضت ساعات وتندى التراب الذي غطي به فليقام الماء في تلك المشارات فياما دائما متّصلا","english":"And the other way [of transplanting rice] is when the earth is cut into divisions and water is introduced into it to stand a handspan high, then the seeds are strewn onto it, and when the earth is soaked by this water the rice is covered with sprinkled soil strewn onto it by the hands until some hours have passed and the soil which has been strewn on it is damp too, and the water shall stand in these beds continuously and without intermission."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to insert, to drive in"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of رَزَّ (razza) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"inserting, driving in"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a faint sound, like that which you can hear from a distance"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Etymology tree\nProto-Indo-Iranian *wriHǰʰíš\nProto-Iranian *wriHǰíš\nProto-Iranian *wrinǰišder.\nAncient Greek ὄρυζα (óruza)bor.\nArabic رز\nBorrowed from Aramaic אֲרוּזָא (ʔăruzzā) / ܐܘܪܘܙܐ (ʔuruzzā), ܪܘܙܐ (rūzā). Doublet of بِرِنْج (birinj).\n\nbears resemblance to Aramaic רָזָ֥א (rāzā)."},"ipa":["/ruzz/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n15348","headword_ar":"رُزٌّ","root":"rz","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aruz~N","text_ar":"اَرُزٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rice:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see the latter word, in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Arz","text_ar":"ارز"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, K.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n15349","headword_ar":"رِزٌّ","root":"rz","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A piercing"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pain"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and rumbling"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the belly: (A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pain"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the belly; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riz~iyzaY","text_ar":"رِزِّيزَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pain, and pressure of the feces:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pressure and motion of the feces"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the belly, (Kt, Mgh, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the effort to pass forth, so that the person who feels it wants to enter the privy; whether it be with a rumbling or without:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kt, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sound of rumbling or the like"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the belly. (As, Mgh, * TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wajadotu","text_ar":"وَجَدْتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY baToniY riz~FA","text_ar":"فِى بَطْنِى رِزًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S, A)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I felt in my belly a piercing"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pain"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and rumbling:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a pain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S: expl. in the KL by the Pers. word"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darod","text_ar":"دَرْد"},{"kind":"text","text":":) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riz~iyzaY","text_ar":"رِزِّيزَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (As, S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pain, and pressure of the feces;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A vehement burning in the mouth"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a camel,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arising from thirst, with pain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A low sound:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any sound that is not vehement:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A 'Obeyd, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sound that one hears from afar;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riz~iyzaY","text_ar":"رِزِّيزَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sound that one hears but knows not what it is:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sound in a more common sense;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehement or slight:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sound;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as of thunder &c.: (S:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sound of thunder;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raziyzN","text_ar":"رَزِيزٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [in measure] like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amiyrN","text_ar":"اَمِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": or the former has a more general application: and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iroziyzN","text_ar":"اـِرْزِيزٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in like manner] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sound:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thunder:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riz~N","text_ar":"رِزٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"braying"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a stallion-camel. (K, * TA.)"}],"source_refs":["A","S","TA","Kt","Mgh","As","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%B1%D8%B2/","headword_ar":"رز","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_36","lexicon_en":"Al-Ṣāḥib bin ʿAbbād, Al-Muḥīṭ fī l-Lugha (d. c. 995 CE)","lexicon_ar":"المحيط في اللغة للصاحب بن عباد","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=93995#26200e","body_html":"<span class=\"title1\">رز</span><br><span>الرّزُّ: الطَّعْنُ، رَزَّهُ رَزًةً. ورَزَزْتُ السِّكَيْنَ والسهْمَ في الحائطِ فارْتَزَّ: أي ثَبَتَ. وأرَزَتِ الجَرَادَةُ: أدْخَلَتْ ذَنَبَهَا في الأرْضِ كَيْ تَبِيْضَ. وارْتَزَّ عَلي عِرْقٌ: انْتَفَضَ.</span><br><span>والرّزُّ: الصَوْتُ تَسْمَعهُ من بَعِيْدٍ. ورَزَتِ السَّماءُ تَرِزُّ رَزّاً: صَوَّتَتْ من المَطَرِ. والرَّزَّةُ من الحَدِيْدِ: مَعْرُوفَةٌ، وهي الرَّزَّاتُ. والإرْزِيْزُ: الرِّعْدَةُ من البَرْدِ. وهي - أيضاً -: بَرَدٌ صِغَارٌ مِثْلُ الحَصَى من الدمَقِ. وطَعْنٌ يَجِدُه الإنسانُ في جَوْفِه. وحُرْقَةٌ من الجُوْع، وكذلك الرِّزُ والرّزَيْزى. وارْتَزَ فلانٌ في رِزِّ فلانٍ: إذا ذَهَبَ مَذْهَبَه وفَعَلَ فِعْلَه. ورَزْرَزْتُ الحِمْلَ: سَوَّيْتَه. ووَطَّاْتُ الأمْرَ ورَزًزْتُه: واحِد. ورَزْرَزْتُ الشيْءَ: حَرَّكْتَه. والرَّزَازُ: لُغَةٌ في الرصَاصِ، كذا قال. والرُّز: لُغَةٌ في الأرُزَ، طَعَامٌ مُرَزَّزٌ: مُعَالَجٌ بالرُزَ.</span>"},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_49","lexicon_en":"Arabic-English Lexicon by Edward William Lane (d. 1876)","lexicon_ar":"المعجم العربي الإنجليزي لإدوارد وليام لين","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=93995#3aebc0","body_html":"<h3>رز</h3><span class=\"sense\">1</span> رَزَّهُ, [<abbr title=\"aorist (shows the vowel of the second consonant of the aorist/muḍāriʿ form)\">aor.</abbr> ـُ <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. n.</abbr> رَزٌّ,] He pierced, stuck, or stabbed, him. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> He stuck, or fastened, or fixed, it, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) into the ground, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>,) or into another thing; (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>;) as, for instance, a nail (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>) or a knife (A) into a wall, (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>,) or a knife into the ground, (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>,) and an arrow into the target. (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b3:</span> رَزَّتِ الجَرَادَةُ, <abbr title=\"aorist (shows the vowel of the second consonant of the aorist/muḍāriʿ form)\">aor.</abbr> ـُ (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>) and رَزِّ, (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. n.</abbr> رَزٌّ (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>) and رُزُوزٌ, (so in a copy of the <abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, but wanting in another,) The locust stuck her tail into the ground, (<abbr title=\"al-Azharī, author of the Tahdhīb\">Az</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) and laid her eggs, (<abbr title=\"al-Azharī, author of the Tahdhīb\">Az</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>,) or to lay her eggs; (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>;) as also ↓ ارزّت. (<abbr title=\"al-Azharī, author of the Tahdhīb\">Az</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">A2:</span> رَزَّ البَابَ, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) <abbr title=\"aorist (shows the vowel of the second consonant of the aorist/muḍāriʿ form)\">aor.</abbr> ـُ <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. n.</abbr> رَزٌّ, (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>,) He furnished the door with a رَزَّة [or staple to receive the bolt of the lock]. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>. <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">A3:</span> رَزَّتِ السَّمَآءُ, (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) <abbr title=\"aorist (shows the vowel of the second consonant of the aorist/muḍāriʿ form)\">aor.</abbr> ـِ (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>,) <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. n.</abbr> رَزٌّ, (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>,) The sky made a sound by reason of rain. (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> رَزَّ is also said of a stallion [i. e. a stallion-camel, meaning He uttered a low braying]: and of thunder [meaning It made a low sound]. (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>.) [See رِزٌّ below.] <span class=\"sub-sense\">b3:</span> And رَزٌّ signifies also The being instantly silent. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) 2 رَزَّزْتُ لَكَ الأَمْرَ, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>,) <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. n.</abbr> تَرْزِيزٌ, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) (<abbr title=\"مَجَازٌ and مَجَازِيٌّ\">tropical</abbr>:) I arranged, or facilitated, for thee the affair. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>. *) And زَرَّزْتُ أَمْرَكَ عِنْدَ فُلَانٍ (<abbr title=\"مَجَازٌ and مَجَازِيٌّ\">tropical</abbr>:) I arranged, or facilitated, thine affair, and put it in a sound, right, or proper, state, (ثَبَّتُّهُ, [or, as in one copy of the <abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, بَيَّنْتُهُ, i. e. made it clear, or plain,]) with such a one. (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">A2:</span> تَرْزِيزٌ also signifies The glazing, or polishing, of paper. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> [See also the <abbr title=\"passive participial noun, إِسْمُ مَفْعُولٍ\">pass. part. n.</abbr>, below: whence it appears that it signifies also The dressing, or preparing, &amp;c., with rice.] <abbr title=\"al-Rawḍ al-Unuf of al-Suhaylī\">R</abbr>. <abbr title=\"quadriliteral-radical verb, فِعْلٌ رُبَاعِيٌّ\">Q.</abbr> 1 رَزْرَزَهُ, (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. n.</abbr> رَزْرَزَةٌ, (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>,) He put it in motion, or in a state of commotion. (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> And He equalized it; namely, a load, or burden; (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>;) made it to counterbalance. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) 4 ارزّت الجَرَادَةُ: see 1.<span class=\"sense\">8</span> ارتزّ It stuck, or became fastened or fixed, into a thing; (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>;) as, for instance, an arrow into the target, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) and into the ground. (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> (assumed <abbr title=\"مَجَازٌ and مَجَازِيٌّ\">tropical</abbr>:) He (a niggardly man) remained fixed in his place, and was tenacious, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, * <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>, * <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>,) and was ashamed and confounded, or speechless and motionless through confusion and shame. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) رُزٌّ <abbr title=\"idem quod (i.e. the same as)\">i. q.</abbr> أَرُزٌّ [i. e. Rice: see the latter word, in art. ارز]. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) رِزٌّ A piercing [pain] and rumbling in the belly: (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>:) or pain in the belly; as also ↓ رِزِّيزَى: (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>:) or pain, and pressure of the feces: (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>:) or the pressure and motion of the feces in the belly, (<abbr title=\"The Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (of al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī)\">KT</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Mughrib of al-Mutarrizī\">Mgh</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>,) in the effort to pass forth, so that the person who feels it wants to enter the privy; whether it be with a rumbling or without: (<abbr title=\"The Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (of al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī)\">KT</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>:) or a sound of rumbling or the like in the belly. (<abbr title=\"al-Aṣmaʿī\">As</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Mughrib of al-Mutarrizī\">Mgh</abbr>, * <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) You say, وَجَدْتُ فِى بَطْنِى رِزًّا (<abbr title=\"al-Aṣmaʿī\">As</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, A) I felt in my belly a piercing [pain] and rumbling: (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>:) or a pain: (<abbr title=\"al-Aṣmaʿī\">As</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>: <abbr title=\"explained\">expl.</abbr> in the <abbr title=\"The Kanz al-Lughah of Ibn Maʿrūf; an Arabic-Persian Dictionary\">KL</abbr> by the <abbr title=\"Persian (Farsi)\">Pers\\.</abbr> word دَرْد:) as also ↓ رِزِّيزَى: (<abbr title=\"al-Aṣmaʿī\">As</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>:) or pain, and pressure of the feces; &amp;c. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> [Hence,] (assumed <abbr title=\"مَجَازٌ and مَجَازِيٌّ\">tropical</abbr>:) A vehement burning in the mouth of a camel, arising from thirst, with pain. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b3:</span> Also A low sound: (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>:) any sound that is not vehement: (A 'Obeyd, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>:) or a sound that one hears from afar; as also ↓ رِزِّيزَى: (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>:) or a sound that one hears but knows not what it is: (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>:) or a sound in a more common sense; (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>;) vehement or slight: (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>:) or a sound; as of thunder &amp;c.: (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>:) or the sound of thunder; (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>;) as also ↓ رَزِيزٌ, [in measure] like أَمِيرٌ: or the former has a more general application: and ↓ إِرْزِيزٌ [in like manner] signifies a sound: and also thunder: (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>:) and رِزٌّ also signifies the braying of a stallion-camel. (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>, * <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) رَزَّةٌ A single piercing; a stick, or stab. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> And A pain in the back. (<abbr title=\"al-Saghānī, author of the ʿUbāb and the Takmilah fī al-Ṣiḥāḥ\">Sgh</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">A2:</span> The iron [meaning the staple] into which [the bolt of] the lock enters: (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>:) so called because [the bolt of] the lock penetrates it: <abbr title=\"plural, جَمْعٌ\">pl.</abbr> رَزَّاتٌ. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) رَزَازٌ <abbr title=\"idem quod (i.e. the same as)\">i. q.</abbr> رَصَاصٌ [generally meaning Lead]: (<abbr title=\"al-Saghānī, author of the ʿUbāb and the Takmilah fī al-Ṣiḥāḥ\">Sgh</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>:) a <abbr title=\"dialect, لُغَةٌ\">dial.</abbr> var. of the latter word. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) رَزِيزٌ: see رِزٌّ.<br><br><span class=\"sub-sense\">A2:</span> Also A certain plant, with which one dyes. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) رَزَّازٌ One who sells, and traffics in, رُزّ [or rice]. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) رِزِّيزَى: see رِزٌّ in three places.<br><br>إِرْزِيزٌ A piercing, sticking, or stabbing, (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>,) such as is firm, or steady. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">A2:</span> A tremour. (<abbr title=\"Thaʿlab, author of the Faṣīḥ\">Th</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> See also رِزٌّ, last sentence.<br><br><span class=\"sub-sense\">A3:</span> Long-sounding. (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">A4:</span> Hail: (<abbr title=\"Thaʿlab, author of the Faṣīḥ\">Th</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>:) or small hail, like snow. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) مَرَزَّةٌ A place in which رُزّ [or rice] is collected together; like the كُدْس of wheat. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) مُرَزَّزٌ Food dressed, prepared, or mixed up, (مُعَالَجٌ,) with رُزّ [or rice]. (<abbr title=\"al-Saghānī, author of the ʿUbāb and the Takmilah fī al-Ṣiḥāḥ\">Sgh</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) and Paper dressed, or prepared, (مُعَالَجٌ,) with رُزّ [or rice]: (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>:) or paper glazed, or polished. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>.)"}]}}